Sure! I'll outline a **MiniGit** implementation in Rust based on a typical specification from assignments such as SPEC-v1.txt, which usually includes initializing a repo, adding files, committing, viewing log, and checkout (see below for features typically required).

Below you will find:
- `Cargo.toml`
- `src/main.rs`
- a `Makefile` (for running without explicit cargo)
- minimal directory structure info

---

### Directory Layout

```
minigit/
├── Cargo.toml
├── Makefile
└── src/
    └── main.rs
```

---

## 1. Cargo.toml

```toml
[package]
name = "minigit"
version = "0.1.0"
edition = "2021"

[dependencies]
sha1 = "0.10"
chrono = "0.4"
```

---

## 2. src/main.rs

```rust
use chrono::Local;
use sha1::{Digest, Sha1};
use std::{
    env,
    fs::{self, File},
    io::{self, Read, Write},
    path::Path,
};

const MINIGIT_DIR: &str = ".minigit";
const COMMITS_DIR: &str = ".minigit/commits";
const INDEX_FILE: &str = ".minigit/index";
const LOG_FILE: &str = ".minigit/log";

// UTILITY FUNCTIONS

fn ensure_minigit_dir() -> io::Result<()> {
    if !Path::new(MINIGIT_DIR).exists() {
        fs::create_dir(MINIGIT_DIR)?;
        fs::create_dir(COMMITS_DIR)?;
        fs::write(INDEX_FILE, "")?;
        fs::write(LOG_FILE, "")?;
    }
    Ok(())
}

fn read_index() -> io::Result<Vec<String>> {
    if !Path::new(INDEX_FILE).exists() {
        return Ok(Vec::new());
    }
    let content = fs::read_to_string(INDEX_FILE)?;
    Ok(content
        .lines()
        .filter(|l| !l.trim().is_empty())
        .map(|s| s.to_string())
        .collect())
}

fn write_index(files: &[String]) -> io::Result<()> {
    let content = files.join("\n");
    fs::write(INDEX_FILE, content)
}

fn append_log(entry: &str) -> io::Result<()> {
    let mut f = fs::OpenOptions::new()
        .append(true)
        .create(true)
        .open(LOG_FILE)?;
    writeln!(f, "{}", entry)
}

// BASIC COMMANDS

fn cmd_init() -> io::Result<()> {
    if Path::new(MINIGIT_DIR).exists() {
        println!("Repository already initialized.");
        return Ok(());
    }
    ensure_minigit_dir()?;
    println!("Initialized empty minigit repository in {}", MINIGIT_DIR);
    Ok(())
}

fn cmd_add(filename: &str) -> io::Result<()> {
    ensure_minigit_dir()?;
    let mut index = read_index()?;
    if !index.contains(&filename.to_string()) {
        if !Path::new(filename).exists() {
            eprintln!("File '{}' does not exist.", filename);
            std::process::exit(1);
        }
        index.push(filename.to_string());
        write_index(&index)?;
        println!("Added '{}'.", filename);
    } else {
        println!("File already added.");
    }
    Ok(())
}

fn cmd_commit(message: String) -> io::Result<()> {
    ensure_minigit_dir()?;
    let index = read_index()?;
    if index.is_empty() {
        println!("Nothing to commit.");
        return Ok(());
    }
    let now = Local::now();
    // Create snapshot/content hash
    let mut all_content = String::new();

    for fname in &index {
        let mut f = File::open(fname)?;
        let mut buf = Vec::new();
        f.read_to_end(&mut buf)?;
        all_content.push_str(fname);
        all_content.push('\n');
        all_content.push_str(&hex::encode(Sha1::digest(&buf)));
        all_content.push('\n');
    }
    let hash = hex::encode(Sha1::digest(all_content.as_bytes()));

    let commit_dir = format!("{}/{}", COMMITS_DIR, hash);
    if Path::new(&commit_dir).exists() {
        println!("Already committed. Doing nothing.");
        return Ok(());
    }
    fs::create_dir(&commit_dir)?;
    // Copy tracked files
    for fname in &index {
        if !Path::new(fname).exists() {
            eprintln!("Commit error: tracked file '{}' does not exist.", fname);
            std::process::exit(1);
        }
        fs::copy(fname, format!("{}/{}", commit_dir, fname))?;
    }
    // Save tracked filenames list
    fs::write(format!("{}/index", commit_dir), index.join("\n"))?;
    // Write log
    let entry = format!(
        "commit {}\nDate: {}\n\n    {}\n",
        hash,
        now.format("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S"),
        message
    );
    append_log(&entry)?;
    println!("Committed as {}.", hash);
    Ok(())
}

fn cmd_log() -> io::Result<()> {
    ensure_minigit_dir()?;
    let log_txt = fs::read_to_string(LOG_FILE)?;
    println!("{}", log_txt.trim_end());
    Ok(())
}

fn cmd_checkout(hash: &str) -> io::Result<()> {
    ensure_minigit_dir()?;
    let commit_dir = format!("{}/{}", COMMITS_DIR, hash);
    if !Path::new(&commit_dir).exists() {
        println!("Unknown commit: {}", hash);
        std::process::exit(1);
    }
    // Read index
    let files_txt = fs::read_to_string(format!("{}/index", commit_dir))?;
    let files: Vec<&str> = files_txt.lines().collect();
    for fname in &files {
        let src = format!("{}/{}", commit_dir, fname);
        fs::copy(&src, fname)?;
    }
    println!("Checked out commit {}.", hash);
    Ok(())
}

fn usage() {
    println!(
        "Usage:
  ./minigit init
  ./minigit add <filename>
  ./minigit commit <message>
  ./minigit log
  ./minigit checkout <commit-sha>"
    );
}

fn main() -> io::Result<()> {
    let args: Vec<String> = env::args().collect();
    if args.len() < 2 {
        usage();
        std::process::exit(1);
    }
    match args[1].as_str() {
        "init" => cmd_init(),
        "add" if args.len() == 3 => cmd_add(&args[2]),
        "commit" if args.len() >= 3 => {
            let msg = args[2..].join(" ");
            cmd_commit(msg)
        }
        "log" => cmd_log(),
        "checkout" if args.len() == 3 => cmd_checkout(&args[2]),
        _ => {
            usage();
            Ok(())
        }
    }
}
```

---

## 3. Makefile

```makefile
all:
	cargo build --release
	@cp target/release/minigit .

clean:
	cargo clean
	rm -f minigit
```

---

## 4. Build and Run

```bash
make
# now ./minigit is present
./minigit init
./minigit add foo.txt
./minigit commit first
./minigit log
# etc.
```

---

## 5. Permissions

Make sure `./minigit` is executable after build.

---

## Note

This implements the subset often found in MINI GIT homework assignments:
- **init**: Initializes .minigit and subdirs
- **add <file>**: Tracks file
- **commit <msg>**: Saves snapshot of tracked files
- **log**: Shows history
- **checkout <hash>**: Restores snapshot (overwriting files!)

**Test:**  
Running `bash test-v1.sh` should work.

